SIMPLE: literally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Literally
<hw>Lit"er*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>According to the
primary and natural import of words; not figuratively; <as>as, a man and
his wife can not be <ex>literally</ex> one flesh</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With close adherence to words; word by
word.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So wild and ungovernable a poet can not be translated
<qex>literally</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Literalness</ent>⟦br⟧
